title: Introductory Microeconomics
description: Theory of how individual consumers and firms behave in a market economy. Emphasis is on evaluating how well markets deliver efficient and fair outcomes.
prerequisite: 15 credit hours or ECON 100 or Pre-Calculus 20 (or equivalent)
